00:00:06.986 --> 00:00:25.960 align:middle line:90%


00:00:25.960 --> 00:00:28.690 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE MORTER: We often hear
the term muscle memory.

00:00:28.690 --> 00:00:31.420 align:middle line:10%
Well, it turns out that it's
not only our muscles that store

00:00:31.420 --> 00:00:33.550 align:middle line:10%
memories but our entire body--

00:00:33.550 --> 00:00:36.700 align:middle line:10%
muscles, organs, blood
vessels, and more.

00:00:36.700 --> 00:00:39.520 align:middle line:84%
And when we experience
traumatic events,

00:00:39.520 --> 00:00:43.210 align:middle line:84%
our bodies hold onto and
suppress these experiences

00:00:43.210 --> 00:00:47.650 align:middle line:84%
in ways that often result
in pain and disease.

00:00:47.650 --> 00:00:50.260 align:middle line:84%
Jonathan Tripodi, a
physical therapist,

00:00:50.260 --> 00:00:54.730 align:middle line:84%
developed a body work program
called Body Memory Recall,

00:00:54.730 --> 00:00:57.640 align:middle line:84%
which facilitates the body's
innate ability to release

00:00:57.640 --> 00:00:59.890 align:middle line:90%
and heal old wounds.

00:00:59.890 --> 00:01:03.310 align:middle line:84%
BMR, as it's known, has
helped countless people

00:01:03.310 --> 00:01:07.720 align:middle line:84%
to come out of survival mode
and enter a self-healing state,

00:01:07.720 --> 00:01:11.260 align:middle line:84%
restoring them to
renewed health, vitality,

00:01:11.260 --> 00:01:13.120 align:middle line:90%
and fulfillment.

00:01:13.120 --> 00:01:13.920 align:middle line:10%
Welcome, Jonathan.

00:01:13.920 --> 00:01:15.170 align:middle line:10%
>>JONATHAN TRIPODI: Thank you.

00:01:15.170 --> 00:01:17.290 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: It's so great
to have you here.

00:01:17.290 --> 00:01:19.150 align:middle line:84%
Can you just tell us
a little bit about,

00:01:19.150 --> 00:01:22.460 align:middle line:84%
what is body memory
to begin with?

00:01:22.460 --> 00:01:23.260 align:middle line:90%
>>TRIPODI: Yeah.

00:01:23.260 --> 00:01:27.580 align:middle line:10%
Concisely, I would say body
memory is those experiences

00:01:27.580 --> 00:01:30.670 align:middle line:10%
from our past that
we experienced

00:01:30.670 --> 00:01:35.080 align:middle line:10%
as overwhelming or painful
that we suppressed as a way

00:01:35.080 --> 00:01:36.760 align:middle line:10%
to survive.

00:01:36.760 --> 00:01:40.710 align:middle line:84%
The suppression is not only
in the mind but in the body.

00:01:40.710 --> 00:01:44.200 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: And when did you first
learn about body memory?

00:01:44.200 --> 00:01:46.540 align:middle line:84%
>>TRIPODI: I'd just got out
of physical therapy school,

00:01:46.540 --> 00:01:48.760 align:middle line:84%
and I attended a
myofascial release workshop

00:01:48.760 --> 00:01:50.200 align:middle line:90%
by John Barnes.

00:01:50.200 --> 00:01:53.110 align:middle line:84%
And it was during that
workshop, through the practice

00:01:53.110 --> 00:01:57.610 align:middle line:84%
of techniques, that I
accessed some body memory.

00:01:57.610 --> 00:02:02.590 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: And how does a
person develop body memory?

00:02:02.590 --> 00:02:04.480 align:middle line:84%
>>TRIPODI: Just
being human, we have

00:02:04.480 --> 00:02:06.580 align:middle line:84%
experiences that are
overwhelming and painful

00:02:06.580 --> 00:02:07.960 align:middle line:90%
throughout our life.

00:02:07.960 --> 00:02:11.110 align:middle line:10%
The ones that occurred in our
childhood we often forget.

00:02:11.110 --> 00:02:14.440 align:middle line:10%
But the ones that we
experience in adulthood

00:02:14.440 --> 00:02:16.630 align:middle line:10%
are the ones we remember.

00:02:16.630 --> 00:02:20.440 align:middle line:84%
But all these experiences
we cope with and survive

00:02:20.440 --> 00:02:21.850 align:middle line:90%
in a very automated way.

00:02:21.850 --> 00:02:22.930 align:middle line:90%
We don't think about it.

00:02:22.930 --> 00:02:24.040 align:middle line:90%
We just survive it.

00:02:24.040 --> 00:02:26.260 align:middle line:84%
And by surviving
it, we suppress it.

00:02:26.260 --> 00:02:28.060 align:middle line:84%
And that's how we
begin to accumulate

00:02:28.060 --> 00:02:29.737 align:middle line:90%
body memory over a lifetime.

00:02:29.737 --> 00:02:31.570 align:middle line:10%
>>SUE: And so how does
somebody know if they

00:02:31.570 --> 00:02:33.730 align:middle line:10%
have this happening with them?

00:02:33.730 --> 00:02:37.930 align:middle line:84%
What are the symptoms that
would reveal, giving someone

00:02:37.930 --> 00:02:40.120 align:middle line:84%
the notion that maybe
something's being held

00:02:40.120 --> 00:02:45.010 align:middle line:84%
in my system here that's keeping
me from moving forward in life?

00:02:45.010 --> 00:02:48.020 align:middle line:84%
>>TRIPODI: Pain is the
most obvious symptom.

00:02:48.020 --> 00:02:51.860 align:middle line:84%
When we suppress memory, memory
actually consists of energy.

00:02:51.860 --> 00:02:53.960 align:middle line:84%
So when energy isn't
flowing through the body,

00:02:53.960 --> 00:02:55.390 align:middle line:90%
it's creating tension.

00:02:55.390 --> 00:02:58.790 align:middle line:84%
And tension over time creates
inflammation and pain.

00:02:58.790 --> 00:03:03.100 align:middle line:10%
So any place in your body that
is painful and chronically

00:03:03.100 --> 00:03:06.790 align:middle line:10%
painful is a good
sign that there's

00:03:06.790 --> 00:03:09.980 align:middle line:10%
a body memory source behind it.

00:03:09.980 --> 00:03:13.630 align:middle line:10%
There's also emotional sources,
like anxiety and depression,

00:03:13.630 --> 00:03:17.410 align:middle line:10%
certainly digestive issues,
breathing problems, circulatory

00:03:17.410 --> 00:03:19.180 align:middle line:10%
or neurological conditions.

00:03:19.180 --> 00:03:21.490 align:middle line:84%
Because body memory
is cellular, it

00:03:21.490 --> 00:03:26.140 align:middle line:84%
can affect every aspect of our
anatomy and creates symptoms.

00:03:26.140 --> 00:03:28.660 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: So we go through
a traumatic experience.

00:03:28.660 --> 00:03:30.940 align:middle line:84%
Our body has a memory
of that experience

00:03:30.940 --> 00:03:32.830 align:middle line:90%
and reacts in some way.

00:03:32.830 --> 00:03:35.890 align:middle line:84%
If it gets stuck in that
pattern of reaction,

00:03:35.890 --> 00:03:39.808 align:middle line:84%
then we're stuck right there
as a memory pattern running us.

00:03:39.808 --> 00:03:41.350 align:middle line:84%
Is this basically
what you're saying?

00:03:41.350 --> 00:03:42.160 align:middle line:84%
>>TRIPODI: You're
absolutely right.

00:03:42.160 --> 00:03:43.450 align:middle line:90%
And the keyword is reaction.

00:03:43.450 --> 00:03:45.560 align:middle line:90%
And the reaction is fear.

00:03:45.560 --> 00:03:48.310 align:middle line:84%
When we're overwhelmed,
we become afraid.

00:03:48.310 --> 00:03:50.500 align:middle line:84%
And so the fear
mechanism is what

00:03:50.500 --> 00:03:54.490 align:middle line:84%
creates the defensive
protective responses that

00:03:54.490 --> 00:03:58.540 align:middle line:84%
begin to store what we're afraid
of, the sensations or emotions,

00:03:58.540 --> 00:04:00.508 align:middle line:90%
into our body.

00:04:00.508 --> 00:04:02.050 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: So it's
producing chemistries,

00:04:02.050 --> 00:04:04.780 align:middle line:84%
and it's producing neurological
patterns, et cetera.

00:04:04.780 --> 00:04:06.080 align:middle line:90%
Is that what's happening here?

00:04:06.080 --> 00:04:06.880 align:middle line:90%
>>TRIPODI: Exactly.

00:04:06.880 --> 00:04:09.460 align:middle line:84%
Once you've survived
a memory, that's

00:04:09.460 --> 00:04:10.870 align:middle line:90%
different than healing it.

00:04:10.870 --> 00:04:15.220 align:middle line:84%
So we continue to remain in
survival mode, even years

00:04:15.220 --> 00:04:18.160 align:middle line:90%
after the original events occur.

00:04:18.160 --> 00:04:21.070 align:middle line:84%
And we also adapt to them,
so they become normal.

00:04:21.070 --> 00:04:24.010 align:middle line:84%
But our body, like you
say, almost like a circuit,

00:04:24.010 --> 00:04:27.130 align:middle line:84%
like a program that's just being
played over and over again,

00:04:27.130 --> 00:04:32.210 align:middle line:84%
is this reaction and defense
to something that was painful.

00:04:32.210 --> 00:04:36.040 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: I think it's really
key to say here twice that you

00:04:36.040 --> 00:04:37.300 align:middle line:90%
can survive a memory.

00:04:37.300 --> 00:04:39.970 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't necessarily
mean that you've healed it.

00:04:39.970 --> 00:04:41.590 align:middle line:84%
If we got through,
it doesn't mean

00:04:41.590 --> 00:04:46.030 align:middle line:84%
that we've turned on a different
form of our body's function.

00:04:46.030 --> 00:04:48.490 align:middle line:84%
But rather, we could be
locked into this pattern

00:04:48.490 --> 00:04:51.250 align:middle line:84%
of defensiveness or fight
or flight or survival

00:04:51.250 --> 00:04:54.070 align:middle line:84%
mechanism that kicks in
during the middle of a trauma

00:04:54.070 --> 00:04:56.530 align:middle line:90%
or some unwanted experience.

00:04:56.530 --> 00:04:57.330 align:middle line:90%
Is this--

00:04:57.330 --> 00:04:57.590 align:middle line:90%
>>TRIPODI: Yes.

00:04:57.590 --> 00:04:58.600 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: --tracking here?

00:04:58.600 --> 00:05:00.550 align:middle line:84%
>>TRIPODI: And if I
were to then define,

00:05:00.550 --> 00:05:04.150 align:middle line:84%
what is a healed memory, it's
one in which you're no longer

00:05:04.150 --> 00:05:05.800 align:middle line:90%
protecting yourself from it.

00:05:05.800 --> 00:05:07.160 align:middle line:90%
You're at peace with it.

00:05:07.160 --> 00:05:09.220 align:middle line:84%
There's no evidence
in your mind or body.

00:05:09.220 --> 00:05:10.655 align:middle line:90%
You're no longer in reaction.

00:05:10.655 --> 00:05:11.530 align:middle line:90%
You're not hardening.

00:05:11.530 --> 00:05:12.662 align:middle line:90%
You're not tensing.

00:05:12.662 --> 00:05:13.870 align:middle line:90%
You're not overwhelmed by it.

00:05:13.870 --> 00:05:15.520 align:middle line:90%
You can talk about it.

00:05:15.520 --> 00:05:17.170 align:middle line:90%
You could cry about it.

00:05:17.170 --> 00:05:18.920 align:middle line:84%
But you're not in
protection around it.

00:05:18.920 --> 00:05:19.720 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: Yeah.

00:05:19.720 --> 00:05:21.550 align:middle line:84%
You've had this
firsthand experience

00:05:21.550 --> 00:05:24.335 align:middle line:84%
of the importance of going
back to a moment in time

00:05:24.335 --> 00:05:26.927 align:middle line:84%
and working it out
differently than how

00:05:26.927 --> 00:05:29.010 align:middle line:84%
you got through the first
time, with this accident

00:05:29.010 --> 00:05:29.927 align:middle line:90%
that you were sharing.

00:05:29.927 --> 00:05:32.830 align:middle line:84%
Can you just give us a
little detail about that

00:05:32.830 --> 00:05:34.830 align:middle line:84%
and show us how
that worked for you?

00:05:34.830 --> 00:05:37.020 align:middle line:84%
>>TRIPODI: Well, at age
21, I developed blood clots

00:05:37.020 --> 00:05:38.160 align:middle line:90%
in my right leg.

00:05:38.160 --> 00:05:41.250 align:middle line:84%
And blood clots embolized
and went to my heart

00:05:41.250 --> 00:05:42.660 align:middle line:90%
and then to my lung.

00:05:42.660 --> 00:05:45.030 align:middle line:90%
And it almost killed me.

00:05:45.030 --> 00:05:47.820 align:middle line:84%
Fortunately, I
survived, and I was told

00:05:47.820 --> 00:05:49.260 align:middle line:90%
it would never happen again.

00:05:49.260 --> 00:05:53.250 align:middle line:84%
Six months later, I had massive
blood clotting in my right leg.

00:05:53.250 --> 00:05:55.830 align:middle line:84%
So that really
sidelined me in my life.

00:05:55.830 --> 00:05:59.130 align:middle line:84%
I was taken out of
college, and I was in bed.

00:05:59.130 --> 00:06:02.670 align:middle line:84%
And I was given a prognosis
that was pretty sad.

00:06:02.670 --> 00:06:07.170 align:middle line:84%
I was going to have
degenerative effects in my leg

00:06:07.170 --> 00:06:11.730 align:middle line:84%
that would cause it to swell and
eventually lead to amputation.

00:06:11.730 --> 00:06:16.320 align:middle line:84%
So fast forward a few more
years later, at age 25, 26,

00:06:16.320 --> 00:06:18.120 align:middle line:84%
I get out of physical
therapy school,

00:06:18.120 --> 00:06:21.450 align:middle line:84%
and I discover myofascial
release and its ability

00:06:21.450 --> 00:06:24.450 align:middle line:84%
to help you access
memory in your body.

00:06:24.450 --> 00:06:27.060 align:middle line:84%
And I began to access
many memories in my body

00:06:27.060 --> 00:06:30.510 align:middle line:84%
but specifically, the one
related to a car accident

00:06:30.510 --> 00:06:31.620 align:middle line:90%
at age five.

00:06:31.620 --> 00:06:34.560 align:middle line:84%
I was walking across the
road to pick up a ball,

00:06:34.560 --> 00:06:39.270 align:middle line:84%
and a car driven by a drunk
driver going 40 miles an hour

00:06:39.270 --> 00:06:43.050 align:middle line:84%
hit me and threw my body
into a neighbor's driveway,

00:06:43.050 --> 00:06:44.430 align:middle line:90%
and I was dead.

00:06:44.430 --> 00:06:46.110 align:middle line:90%
My right leg was fractured.

00:06:46.110 --> 00:06:49.680 align:middle line:90%
I had broken bones in my ribs.

00:06:49.680 --> 00:06:52.770 align:middle line:84%
My mother heard the thud and
came out and resuscitated me

00:06:52.770 --> 00:06:54.670 align:middle line:90%
and brought me back to life.

00:06:54.670 --> 00:06:59.130 align:middle line:84%
And as a young kid,
you bounce back.

00:06:59.130 --> 00:07:03.630 align:middle line:84%
But what I hadn't
realized until age 26, 27,

00:07:03.630 --> 00:07:06.810 align:middle line:84%
when I started getting
body memory work done

00:07:06.810 --> 00:07:09.720 align:middle line:84%
to my body, specifically
this right leg,

00:07:09.720 --> 00:07:14.100 align:middle line:84%
I started to access these
memories of the accident.

00:07:14.100 --> 00:07:16.160 align:middle line:84%
The more I cleared
these memories

00:07:16.160 --> 00:07:19.320 align:middle line:84%
of the accident and a
lot of childhood emotions

00:07:19.320 --> 00:07:22.710 align:middle line:84%
that had been
suppressed, the swelling

00:07:22.710 --> 00:07:24.330 align:middle line:84%
in my leg from all
the blood clots

00:07:24.330 --> 00:07:28.260 align:middle line:84%
began to go down and
eventually disappear entirely.

00:07:28.260 --> 00:07:31.680 align:middle line:84%
And there was about a
15-year healing process

00:07:31.680 --> 00:07:34.650 align:middle line:84%
that led to a very
healthy right leg--

00:07:34.650 --> 00:07:38.800 align:middle line:90%
no degeneration, no amputation.

00:07:38.800 --> 00:07:42.150 align:middle line:84%
And for me, it helped me to
discover these innate healing

00:07:42.150 --> 00:07:45.720 align:middle line:84%
abilities that we all
have to transform our past

00:07:45.720 --> 00:07:49.550 align:middle line:84%
and get it out of our body and
actually regenerate ourselves.

00:07:49.550 --> 00:07:50.610 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: Beautiful.

00:07:50.610 --> 00:07:54.990 align:middle line:84%
What would you say happens
when we start to clear

00:07:54.990 --> 00:07:56.790 align:middle line:90%
the effects of these memories?

00:07:56.790 --> 00:07:58.930 align:middle line:84%
What is it that's
happening there?

00:07:58.930 --> 00:08:01.597 align:middle line:90%
How is that unfolding?

00:08:01.597 --> 00:08:03.180 align:middle line:84%
How does healing
happen because you're

00:08:03.180 --> 00:08:06.498 align:middle line:90%
clearing a memory pattern?

00:08:06.498 --> 00:08:08.790 align:middle line:84%
>>TRIPODI: What happens is
these memories that we store

00:08:08.790 --> 00:08:11.490 align:middle line:84%
really are creating chaos
and stress in our body.

00:08:11.490 --> 00:08:14.190 align:middle line:84%
We're taking a painful
or stressful experience

00:08:14.190 --> 00:08:17.080 align:middle line:84%
and taking that,
encapsulating it in some way,

00:08:17.080 --> 00:08:19.020 align:middle line:90%
and storing it in our body.

00:08:19.020 --> 00:08:20.790 align:middle line:90%
So our body's reacting to it.

00:08:20.790 --> 00:08:22.380 align:middle line:84%
We've talked about
physical tensions.

00:08:22.380 --> 00:08:25.000 align:middle line:84%
But also, neurologically,
it creates stress.

00:08:25.000 --> 00:08:27.900 align:middle line:84%
And so when you
release body memory,

00:08:27.900 --> 00:08:29.470 align:middle line:90%
you're releasing stress.

00:08:29.470 --> 00:08:31.170 align:middle line:84%
So one of the
immediate effects is

00:08:31.170 --> 00:08:33.690 align:middle line:84%
that you find you become
more calm and more

00:08:33.690 --> 00:08:37.320 align:middle line:84%
peaceful with each
memory that's released.

00:08:37.320 --> 00:08:39.270 align:middle line:84%
Also, your body
becomes more relaxed.

00:08:39.270 --> 00:08:42.870 align:middle line:84%
The tension that was created
from these memories is gone.

00:08:42.870 --> 00:08:45.690 align:middle line:84%
And so now those
muscles, that tight neck

00:08:45.690 --> 00:08:47.490 align:middle line:84%
and the tight jaw
and the tight back

00:08:47.490 --> 00:08:52.330 align:middle line:84%
and those painful places in your
body aren't hurting anymore.

00:08:52.330 --> 00:08:57.390 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: Why would you think it
necessary for a person to dive

00:08:57.390 --> 00:09:00.720 align:middle line:84%
in and clear these
things, these body

00:09:00.720 --> 00:09:05.760 align:middle line:84%
memories, if they're not
having particular symptoms

00:09:05.760 --> 00:09:06.960 align:middle line:90%
or patterns?

00:09:06.960 --> 00:09:10.190 align:middle line:84%
Is there a benefit
to that as well?

00:09:10.190 --> 00:09:11.040 align:middle line:90%
>>TRIPODI: Yeah.

00:09:11.040 --> 00:09:13.680 align:middle line:84%
You don't necessarily have
to have physical symptoms

00:09:13.680 --> 00:09:18.120 align:middle line:84%
or overt chronic pain to
be carrying body memory.

00:09:18.120 --> 00:09:20.340 align:middle line:84%
You can begin to look at
your life on other levels,

00:09:20.340 --> 00:09:22.290 align:middle line:90%
like emotionally and mentally.

00:09:22.290 --> 00:09:24.720 align:middle line:90%
So the idea is, are you happy?

00:09:24.720 --> 00:09:27.330 align:middle line:90%
Are you fulfilled?

00:09:27.330 --> 00:09:30.840 align:middle line:84%
Do you feel like you are being
guided by a sense of purpose

00:09:30.840 --> 00:09:32.100 align:middle line:90%
in this life?

00:09:32.100 --> 00:09:36.120 align:middle line:84%
Are you able to give
and receive love freely?

00:09:36.120 --> 00:09:39.240 align:middle line:84%
Do you feel like you have
a wise part of your nature

00:09:39.240 --> 00:09:40.620 align:middle line:84%
that is guiding
you in your life,

00:09:40.620 --> 00:09:44.310 align:middle line:84%
or are you constantly
relying on your intellect

00:09:44.310 --> 00:09:46.940 align:middle line:84%
and your logical memory
mind to figure things out?

00:09:46.940 --> 00:09:47.740 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: That's huge.

00:09:47.740 --> 00:09:49.540 align:middle line:84%
>>TRIPODI: And so
body memory impacts

00:09:49.540 --> 00:09:52.740 align:middle line:84%
this on every level-- physical,
emotional, your heart,

00:09:52.740 --> 00:09:54.720 align:middle line:90%
your voice, your spirit.

00:09:54.720 --> 00:09:57.450 align:middle line:84%
And so releasing
body memory can begin

00:09:57.450 --> 00:10:01.440 align:middle line:84%
to help you reconnect
with and reaccess

00:10:01.440 --> 00:10:03.660 align:middle line:84%
these parts of your
nature and bring them

00:10:03.660 --> 00:10:06.040 align:middle line:90%
to a level of full potential.

00:10:06.040 --> 00:10:06.840 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: Perfect.

00:10:06.840 --> 00:10:10.140 align:middle line:84%
What is necessary to
clear these patterns?

00:10:10.140 --> 00:10:11.230 align:middle line:90%
How do we do that?

00:10:11.230 --> 00:10:13.563 align:middle line:84%
>>TRIPODI: First, we have to
get conscious of what we're

00:10:13.563 --> 00:10:15.970 align:middle line:84%
unconscious of, because
when we store body memory,

00:10:15.970 --> 00:10:19.140 align:middle line:84%
part of the protective
mechanism is that we disconnect

00:10:19.140 --> 00:10:20.040 align:middle line:90%
our awareness.

00:10:20.040 --> 00:10:21.390 align:middle line:90%
We don't know it's there.

00:10:21.390 --> 00:10:22.930 align:middle line:90%
We feel pretty good.

00:10:22.930 --> 00:10:24.490 align:middle line:90%
You don't-- right?

00:10:24.490 --> 00:10:27.580 align:middle line:84%
But the challenge is, that helps
us to survive but not to heal,

00:10:27.580 --> 00:10:28.960 align:middle line:90%
as you mentioned earlier.

00:10:28.960 --> 00:10:34.000 align:middle line:84%
So first step is to reconnect
awareness to your body.

00:10:34.000 --> 00:10:37.360 align:middle line:84%
Feel into your body and
begin to get access.

00:10:37.360 --> 00:10:39.820 align:middle line:90%
What does it feel like in there?

00:10:39.820 --> 00:10:40.990 align:middle line:90%
Is it tense?

00:10:40.990 --> 00:10:42.670 align:middle line:90%
Is it stressful?

00:10:42.670 --> 00:10:44.470 align:middle line:90%
Is it scary?

00:10:44.470 --> 00:10:45.940 align:middle line:90%
Is it sad?

00:10:45.940 --> 00:10:47.530 align:middle line:90%
Is it happy?

00:10:47.530 --> 00:10:51.550 align:middle line:84%
How does it really feel to be
in your body, in your neck,

00:10:51.550 --> 00:10:53.470 align:middle line:90%
in your belly, in your heart?

00:10:53.470 --> 00:10:55.000 align:middle line:90%
What does it feel like?

00:10:55.000 --> 00:10:56.890 align:middle line:84%
And what happens
in this process,

00:10:56.890 --> 00:11:02.050 align:middle line:84%
as you begin to connect with
these fears that are protecting

00:11:02.050 --> 00:11:06.070 align:middle line:84%
you from events in your
past, now the next step

00:11:06.070 --> 00:11:10.300 align:middle line:84%
is to overcome the fear, meaning
let go of the protection.

00:11:10.300 --> 00:11:13.150 align:middle line:84%
Start to surrender to
what it is that you

00:11:13.150 --> 00:11:16.630 align:middle line:84%
were previously afraid of,
and maybe currently afraid of.

00:11:16.630 --> 00:11:18.850 align:middle line:84%
And as you do that, the
self-healing process

00:11:18.850 --> 00:11:19.990 align:middle line:90%
starts to take place.

00:11:19.990 --> 00:11:23.020 align:middle line:84%
And the very thing that you've
been protecting yourself from,

00:11:23.020 --> 00:11:25.870 align:middle line:84%
and specifically,
physical sensations

00:11:25.870 --> 00:11:28.570 align:middle line:84%
that are painful
and emotions, when

00:11:28.570 --> 00:11:33.700 align:middle line:84%
you begin to overcome
that fear, those energies

00:11:33.700 --> 00:11:37.150 align:middle line:84%
of those sensations and
emotions come up to the surface.

00:11:37.150 --> 00:11:41.290 align:middle line:84%
And they simply have one
agenda, to be accepted,

00:11:41.290 --> 00:11:43.270 align:middle line:90%
felt, and released.

00:11:43.270 --> 00:11:46.420 align:middle line:84%
And in that process,
your body may shake.

00:11:46.420 --> 00:11:47.440 align:middle line:90%
It could tremble.

00:11:47.440 --> 00:11:48.580 align:middle line:90%
It could twitch.

00:11:48.580 --> 00:11:50.530 align:middle line:90%
It can get hot or cold.

00:11:50.530 --> 00:11:54.040 align:middle line:84%
Certainly, all forms of emotion
can come to the surface.

00:11:54.040 --> 00:11:58.810 align:middle line:84%
And I often let people
know that if you

00:11:58.810 --> 00:12:01.390 align:middle line:84%
want to see a perfect model
of what it is to release body

00:12:01.390 --> 00:12:05.650 align:middle line:90%
memory, observe a two-year-old.

00:12:05.650 --> 00:12:07.960 align:middle line:84%
Look at these young
kids before they have

00:12:07.960 --> 00:12:10.120 align:middle line:90%
learned to be afraid to feel.

00:12:10.120 --> 00:12:15.100 align:middle line:84%
Watch how they fluidly express
their joy and their pain,

00:12:15.100 --> 00:12:19.690 align:middle line:84%
their fear and their sadness,
how it just rolls through them.

00:12:19.690 --> 00:12:21.370 align:middle line:90%
And what happens?

00:12:21.370 --> 00:12:23.680 align:middle line:90%
They feel it and they move on.

00:12:23.680 --> 00:12:25.530 align:middle line:90%
They go from being absolutely--

00:12:25.530 --> 00:12:26.530 align:middle line:90%
they skinned their knee.

00:12:26.530 --> 00:12:27.280 align:middle line:90%
They're in pain.

00:12:27.280 --> 00:12:27.850 align:middle line:90%
They're frightened.

00:12:27.850 --> 00:12:28.830 align:middle line:90%
They're sad.

00:12:28.830 --> 00:12:30.670 align:middle line:90%
They feel it, they release it.

00:12:30.670 --> 00:12:32.590 align:middle line:90%
They get up and go play again.

00:12:32.590 --> 00:12:36.370 align:middle line:10%
So this is what we're
up against as adults,

00:12:36.370 --> 00:12:40.960 align:middle line:10%
is revisiting these fears
around sensation and emotion

00:12:40.960 --> 00:12:43.690 align:middle line:10%
and talking ourself
into, maybe it's

00:12:43.690 --> 00:12:47.150 align:middle line:10%
going to be OK if I can
just let myself feel it.

00:12:47.150 --> 00:12:47.950 align:middle line:90%
Does it hurt?

00:12:47.950 --> 00:12:49.570 align:middle line:90%
Yes, it does.

00:12:49.570 --> 00:12:52.630 align:middle line:84%
What happens as the hurt
leaves your body is you

00:12:52.630 --> 00:12:55.510 align:middle line:90%
begin to transform the hurt.

00:12:55.510 --> 00:12:58.930 align:middle line:84%
You become more free of it,
and you become at peace.

00:12:58.930 --> 00:13:01.570 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes our
pains from our past

00:13:01.570 --> 00:13:05.290 align:middle line:84%
have lessons, little
insights, things to teach us.

00:13:05.290 --> 00:13:07.090 align:middle line:84%
And we don't get
access to those lessons

00:13:07.090 --> 00:13:10.990 align:middle line:84%
when it's still being
protected and defended.

00:13:10.990 --> 00:13:12.620 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: I do similar
work to this.

00:13:12.620 --> 00:13:16.300 align:middle line:10%
And one of the things that
people initially will say

00:13:16.300 --> 00:13:21.220 align:middle line:10%
is that they don't
want to feel the pain.

00:13:21.220 --> 00:13:23.290 align:middle line:10%
I'm always encouraging
them to get in their body

00:13:23.290 --> 00:13:25.110 align:middle line:10%
and not be in
their head so much.

00:13:25.110 --> 00:13:28.280 align:middle line:10%
And people are like, well,
it doesn't feel good.

00:13:28.280 --> 00:13:30.520 align:middle line:84%
So can you offer
some suggestions

00:13:30.520 --> 00:13:32.980 align:middle line:84%
to our viewers that
might be thinking,

00:13:32.980 --> 00:13:35.300 align:middle line:84%
you know, I'm always trying
to get away from this pain

00:13:35.300 --> 00:13:36.100 align:middle line:90%
that I'm feeling.

00:13:36.100 --> 00:13:38.100 align:middle line:84%
And now you're telling
me I should drop in there

00:13:38.100 --> 00:13:39.190 align:middle line:90%
and feel it.

00:13:39.190 --> 00:13:40.050 align:middle line:90%
How?

00:13:40.050 --> 00:13:41.057 align:middle line:90%
How?

00:13:41.057 --> 00:13:42.640 align:middle line:84%
>>TRIPODI: Well,
first I want to honor

00:13:42.640 --> 00:13:46.030 align:middle line:90%
the fact that we are afraid.

00:13:46.030 --> 00:13:50.980 align:middle line:84%
So that doesn't make you
broken or a failure or wrong.

00:13:50.980 --> 00:13:52.240 align:middle line:90%
It makes you human.

00:13:52.240 --> 00:13:56.620 align:middle line:84%
So we want to be able to start
to cultivate some compassion

00:13:56.620 --> 00:13:59.080 align:middle line:90%
for what it is to be human.

00:13:59.080 --> 00:14:01.060 align:middle line:90%
And it's not easy.

00:14:01.060 --> 00:14:03.700 align:middle line:84%
We have capacity, an
emotional capacity,

00:14:03.700 --> 00:14:04.960 align:middle line:90%
to feel things very deeply.

00:14:04.960 --> 00:14:07.010 align:middle line:84%
And that can be
overwhelming at times.

00:14:07.010 --> 00:14:09.320 align:middle line:90%
So the fear is very natural.

00:14:09.320 --> 00:14:12.550 align:middle line:84%
But what I want to
bring to the world

00:14:12.550 --> 00:14:16.540 align:middle line:84%
and help people to realize, as
it was brought to my attention

00:14:16.540 --> 00:14:21.130 align:middle line:84%
way back when, is that you
also have another potential.

00:14:21.130 --> 00:14:23.800 align:middle line:84%
And that potential
is transformation.

00:14:23.800 --> 00:14:25.600 align:middle line:84%
There's a part of
your nature that

00:14:25.600 --> 00:14:31.120 align:middle line:84%
is absolutely fearless, wise,
and loving and compassionate.

00:14:31.120 --> 00:14:33.820 align:middle line:84%
And we lose touch with
that part of our nature

00:14:33.820 --> 00:14:38.620 align:middle line:84%
when we get too obsessed
with what we're afraid of.

00:14:38.620 --> 00:14:41.780 align:middle line:84%
And we identify with our
fear as if that's me.

00:14:41.780 --> 00:14:43.090 align:middle line:90%
I'm a fearful person.

00:14:43.090 --> 00:14:46.270 align:middle line:84%
I would say, yes, you
are capable of fear.

00:14:46.270 --> 00:14:51.550 align:middle line:84%
But I want to let you know that
there is a part of your nature

00:14:51.550 --> 00:14:55.030 align:middle line:84%
that isn't afraid,
and it's ready to help

00:14:55.030 --> 00:14:57.310 align:middle line:84%
you transform everything
that ever happened

00:14:57.310 --> 00:15:01.120 align:middle line:84%
to you in your life and restore
you to a very vital, healthy,

00:15:01.120 --> 00:15:03.460 align:middle line:84%
and powerful place
so you can begin

00:15:03.460 --> 00:15:08.500 align:middle line:84%
leading your life from a place
of purpose and fulfillment

00:15:08.500 --> 00:15:10.200 align:middle line:90%
rather than in defense and fear.

00:15:10.200 --> 00:15:11.000 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: Yes.

00:15:11.000 --> 00:15:14.260 align:middle line:84%
It's a very important time
in our culture for people

00:15:14.260 --> 00:15:17.470 align:middle line:84%
to identify that
they can transform

00:15:17.470 --> 00:15:22.330 align:middle line:84%
these painful, fearful
patterns like never before.

00:15:22.330 --> 00:15:23.970 align:middle line:90%
It's upon us at this time.

00:15:23.970 --> 00:15:28.208 align:middle line:84%
So what is science having to
say in support of this paradigm

00:15:28.208 --> 00:15:29.250 align:middle line:90%
that you're working with?

00:15:29.250 --> 00:15:31.500 align:middle line:84%
>>TRIPODI: Science is just
skyrocketing right now

00:15:31.500 --> 00:15:32.560 align:middle line:90%
on this topic.

00:15:32.560 --> 00:15:34.750 align:middle line:84%
And so I can hardly
keep up with it.

00:15:34.750 --> 00:15:39.540 align:middle line:84%
But I will say that the
field of biophysics, which

00:15:39.540 --> 00:15:42.630 align:middle line:84%
