bringing touch to the body

00:17:51.870 --> 00:17:56.340 align:middle line:84%
and specifically to the places
in the body where it's gotten

00:17:56.340 --> 00:17:59.820 align:middle line:90%
hard or restricted or painful.

00:17:59.820 --> 00:18:04.240 align:middle line:84%
And it's inviting a change to
take place in those tissues.

00:18:04.240 --> 00:18:08.910 align:middle line:84%
So when you place your hands
on these areas of the body,

00:18:08.910 --> 00:18:13.170 align:middle line:84%
it not only stimulates the
physical tissues and fluids

00:18:13.170 --> 00:18:16.560 align:middle line:84%
to begin to soften
and release, but it

00:18:16.560 --> 00:18:20.190 align:middle line:84%
begins to touch and connect with
the person inside the tissues

00:18:20.190 --> 00:18:21.390 align:middle line:90%
and the fluids.

00:18:21.390 --> 00:18:23.040 align:middle line:90%
There's a person-- it's us.

00:18:23.040 --> 00:18:23.950 align:middle line:90%
It's our energy.

00:18:23.950 --> 00:18:28.530 align:middle line:84%
Our essence is actually embedded
within our tissues and fluids.

00:18:28.530 --> 00:18:31.385 align:middle line:84%
And it's that person
that's afraid,

00:18:31.385 --> 00:18:32.760 align:middle line:84%
and they're afraid
of things that

00:18:32.760 --> 00:18:34.470 align:middle line:90%
have happened in their past.

00:18:34.470 --> 00:18:37.540 align:middle line:84%
And they're storing that in
their fluids and tissues.

00:18:37.540 --> 00:18:42.210 align:middle line:84%
So the touch is really very
specific, in that it's gentle,

00:18:42.210 --> 00:18:43.560 align:middle line:90%
it's loving, it's connected.

00:18:43.560 --> 00:18:45.630 align:middle line:90%
It's not imposing or forceful.

00:18:45.630 --> 00:18:48.780 align:middle line:84%
And this helps a person
to feel safe, so safe

00:18:48.780 --> 00:18:52.920 align:middle line:84%
that they not only relax, but
they encounter those defense

00:18:52.920 --> 00:18:56.010 align:middle line:84%
systems that have been
active for many years.

00:18:56.010 --> 00:18:59.220 align:middle line:84%
And it helps them feel safe
enough to let them down.

00:18:59.220 --> 00:19:01.920 align:middle line:84%
And when that happens,
you get that transmission

00:19:01.920 --> 00:19:04.950 align:middle line:84%
of suppressed energy
and that release.

00:19:04.950 --> 00:19:06.730 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: Healing presence
in that safety.

00:19:06.730 --> 00:19:07.530 align:middle line:90%
>>TRIPODI: Yes.

00:19:07.530 --> 00:19:08.760 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: Wonderful.

00:19:08.760 --> 00:19:11.180 align:middle line:84%
So how did you go
about developing

00:19:11.180 --> 00:19:12.570 align:middle line:90%
the actual procedure?

00:19:12.570 --> 00:19:14.340 align:middle line:84%
You mentioned that
it's a combination

00:19:14.340 --> 00:19:15.570 align:middle line:90%
of a lot of different things.

00:19:15.570 --> 00:19:17.070 align:middle line:84%
But just tell us
about your process.

00:19:17.070 --> 00:19:17.870 align:middle line:90%
>>TRIPODI: Sure.

00:19:17.870 --> 00:19:20.190 align:middle line:84%
So I started out with my
physical therapy degree,

00:19:20.190 --> 00:19:22.770 align:middle line:84%
and then it was after
physical therapy school

00:19:22.770 --> 00:19:26.130 align:middle line:84%
that I started training
in weekend seminars

00:19:26.130 --> 00:19:27.840 align:middle line:90%
in myofascial release.

00:19:27.840 --> 00:19:30.150 align:middle line:84%
Myofascial release
taught by John Barnes

00:19:30.150 --> 00:19:33.420 align:middle line:84%
has been a significant
component to my work.

00:19:33.420 --> 00:19:35.160 align:middle line:84%
And then I trained
in other techniques,

00:19:35.160 --> 00:19:37.890 align:middle line:84%
like craniosacral therapy
and visceral manipulation.

00:19:37.890 --> 00:19:41.080 align:middle line:84%
But all of these techniques
had one thing in common.

00:19:41.080 --> 00:19:44.460 align:middle line:84%
They all interacted with the
body and the connective tissue

00:19:44.460 --> 00:19:45.330 align:middle line:90%
of the body.

00:19:45.330 --> 00:19:48.330 align:middle line:84%
But also, they touch
the body in a way

00:19:48.330 --> 00:19:51.840 align:middle line:84%
that help people to access
these protective responses

00:19:51.840 --> 00:19:55.230 align:middle line:84%
and release them and get that
body memory component out.

00:19:55.230 --> 00:19:57.600 align:middle line:84%
So after training in many
different techniques,

00:19:57.600 --> 00:20:02.130 align:middle line:84%
I just thought I would put them
all together into one approach.

00:20:02.130 --> 00:20:06.270 align:middle line:84%
My real intention was to
try to bring body memory

00:20:06.270 --> 00:20:09.540 align:middle line:84%
to as many people as possible
and the healing of body memory

00:20:09.540 --> 00:20:11.230 align:middle line:90%
to as many people as possible.

00:20:11.230 --> 00:20:14.400 align:middle line:84%
And I just think all of
those technical terms--

00:20:14.400 --> 00:20:16.740 align:middle line:84%
myofascial release,
craniosacral therapy--

00:20:16.740 --> 00:20:19.020 align:middle line:84%
they don't mean anything
to the layperson.

00:20:19.020 --> 00:20:22.350 align:middle line:84%
But body memory and body
memory transformation

