00:24:50.600 --> 00:24:53.090 align:middle line:84%
Can you just drop into
a little definition

00:24:53.090 --> 00:24:55.452 align:middle line:84%
there to allow-- make
sure all of our viewers

00:24:55.452 --> 00:24:56.660 align:middle line:90%
get what we're talking about?

00:24:56.660 --> 00:24:58.197 align:middle line:84%
>>TRIPODI: Well,
you said it nicely.

00:24:58.197 --> 00:24:59.780 align:middle line:84%
I went through
physical therapy school

00:24:59.780 --> 00:25:02.570 align:middle line:84%
and still had no concept of
what connective tissue is.

00:25:02.570 --> 00:25:05.390 align:middle line:84%
So just so everybody
knows, this was not

00:25:05.390 --> 00:25:10.250 align:middle line:84%
standard information in health
classes or biology classes.

00:25:10.250 --> 00:25:13.550 align:middle line:84%
This is a system that got
overlooked and got put

00:25:13.550 --> 00:25:16.190 align:middle line:84%
on the sidelines as
not an important tissue

00:25:16.190 --> 00:25:18.590 align:middle line:84%
and is now being elevated
as maybe the most

00:25:18.590 --> 00:25:20.930 align:middle line:90%
important system in the body.

00:25:20.930 --> 00:25:24.080 align:middle line:84%
First of all, connective
tissue is a protein.

00:25:24.080 --> 00:25:28.600 align:middle line:84%
It's a chain of proteins
that has a beginning, which

00:25:28.600 --> 00:25:30.580 align:middle line:84%
is at the top of your
head, and an end, which

00:25:30.580 --> 00:25:32.150 align:middle line:90%
is at the bottom of your feet.

00:25:32.150 --> 00:25:35.320 align:middle line:84%
It's a continuous
network of proteins

00:25:35.320 --> 00:25:41.950 align:middle line:84%
that looks like white, stringy,
web-like tissue very randomly

00:25:41.950 --> 00:25:43.840 align:middle line:90%
organized in the body.

00:25:43.840 --> 00:25:47.470 align:middle line:84%
So it has connective functions
and that it connects everything

00:25:47.470 --> 00:25:48.790 align:middle line:90%
to everything--

00:25:48.790 --> 00:25:52.030 align:middle line:84%
blood vessels to
bones, bones to organs.

00:25:52.030 --> 00:25:54.190 align:middle line:90%
It connects cells to cells.

00:25:54.190 --> 00:25:55.400 align:middle line:90%
It connects everything.

00:25:55.400 --> 00:25:57.280 align:middle line:84%
But what's being
discovered now is

00:25:57.280 --> 00:25:59.560 align:middle line:84%
it not only has
connective functions,

00:25:59.560 --> 00:26:02.680 align:middle line:84%
but it has conductive
functions of energy.

00:26:02.680 --> 00:26:06.970 align:middle line:84%
And inside connective tissue,
the fibers are hollow,

00:26:06.970 --> 00:26:10.090 align:middle line:90%
and they have fluid inside.

00:26:10.090 --> 00:26:13.520 align:middle line:84%
Strolling Under the Skin
is a fascinating video,

00:26:13.520 --> 00:26:16.240 align:middle line:84%
the first ever that
begins to show in a living

00:26:16.240 --> 00:26:18.790 align:middle line:84%
body with a small
little telescope what

00:26:18.790 --> 00:26:20.440 align:middle line:90%
living fascia looks like.

00:26:20.440 --> 00:26:24.530 align:middle line:84%
So I recommend you look that
up, Strolling Under the Skin.

00:26:24.530 --> 00:26:27.400 align:middle line:84%
And you'll see the fluid
moving through these fibers

00:26:27.400 --> 00:26:28.960 align:middle line:90%
